# 57edec43c8e7470a9776b3530c38b314
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_cop.en.rst:28
msgid ""
":program:`traffic_cop` is a watchdog program that is responsible for "
"starting :ref:`traffic_manager` and :ref:`traffic_server` and monitoring "
"them for responsiveness. If either of these processes are determined to "
"be unresponsive, :program:`traffic_cop` will kill and restart them."
msgstr ""

# e5b251d3def24a67a78433efbfc7311c
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_cop.en.rst:34
msgid ""
"On Linux, :program:`traffic_cop` will also monitor available memory and "
"swap space, restarting the watched processes if the available memory "
"falls below a minimum threshold. The memory thresholds can be configured "
"with the :ts:cv:`proxy.config.cop.linux_min_swapfree_kb` and "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.cop.linux_min_memfree_kb` variables."
msgstr ""

